FIO-01  |   Race condition - Opening one file but removing another file.
FIO-02  |   Canonicalize all user input before it is processed.
FIO-03  |   Don't accidentally overwrite files you don't want to overwrite.
FIO-04  |   Race condition - Verify file attributes better before processing a file.
FIO-06  |   Access permissions while opening files.
FIO-08  |   Removing a file from the disk. Both methods equally effective.
FIO-10  |   Renaming a file when it already exists.
FIO-11  |   Ensure that the correct flags for fopen() to avoid segfaults.
FIO-13  |   Ensure that file position indicators are adjusted properly between calls to ungetc().
